To the Dispute Resolution Department:

I previously submitted a dispute under 15 U.S.C. §1681i regarding the
above-referenced account. Your investigation concluded that the
disputed information was "verified."

Pursuant to 15 U.S.C. §1681i(a)(7), I am requesting a description of
the procedure used to determine the accuracy and completeness of the
information, including the business name, address, and telephone
number (if reasonably available) of any furnisher of information
contacted in connection with the reinvestigation.

If your "verification" consisted of resending the data to the same
furnisher and recording its response without independent review, the
reinvestigation does not satisfy the "reasonable" standard the FCRA
requires under §1681i(a)(1) and Cushman v. Trans Union Corp., 115
F.3d 220 (3d Cir. 1997).

I expect your written response within the 15-day window specified in
§1681i(a)(7). If a substantive response is not provided, I reserve
all remedies available under §1681n and §1681o.

Sincerely,


{{ profile.name }}
